        <qualifiedname>settings_mgmt_access::name</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Key name for accesses (only set for <ref refid="group__mcumgr__callback__api__settings__mgmt_1gga40c179f978718409c7db43448efc8f47aea0d3b2628423306fbb4d52718d7af00" kindref="member">SETTINGS_ACCESS_READ</ref>, <ref refid="group__mcumgr__callback__api__settings__mgmt_1gga40c179f978718409c7db43448efc8f47a614d170f1bdd53361576fd7c73b7c590" kindref="member">SETTINGS_ACCESS_WRITE</ref>, <ref refid="group__mcumgr__callback__api__settings__mgmt_1gga40c179f978718409c7db43448efc8f47a1d4e86a55ad3d9869b0185cc0b4d9dbd" kindref="member">SETTINGS_ACCESS_DELETE</ref> and <ref refid="group__mcumgr__callback__api__settings__mgmt_1gga40c179f978718409c7db43448efc8f47a37c25f343771851dab3aa4f99c97e543" kindref="member">SETTINGS_ACCESS_SAVE</ref>). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Note that this can be changed by handlers to redirect settings access if needed (as long as it does not exceed the maximum setting string size) if CONFIG_MCUMGR_GRP_SETTINGS_BUFFER_TYPE_STACK is selected, of maximum size CONFIG_MCUMGR_GRP_SETTINGS_NAME_LEN.</para>
<para>Note: This string <emphasis>must</emphasis> be NULL terminated. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
